title: Crash shuts down busy Gwinnett intersection
text:
Crash shuts down busy Gwinnett intersection Crash shuts down busy Gwinnett intersection View Caption Hide Caption A crash shut down the intersection of Jimmy Carter and Peachtree Industrial boulevards Thursday. JOHN SPINK / JSPINK@AJC.COM Story Highlights The crash possibly started with a car race. 
The intersection of Jimmy Carter and Peachtree Industrial boulevards is expected to be closed most the day after a crash brought down power lines. Power lines down and intersection closed: Jimmy Carter Blvd. at P'tree Ind. Blvd. @LizArtzWSB on scene, says avoid the area. #ATLtraffic pic.twitter.com/LGvApReFkG — AJC WSB Traffic (@ajcwsbtraffic) February 23, 2017 
The crash possibly started with a car race about 2:15 a.m., Gwinnett police said. A crash shut down the intersection of Jimmy Carter and Peachtree Industrial boulevards Thursday. JOHN SPINK / JSPINK@AJC.COM 
Drivers are urged to avoid the area, according to the WSB 24-hour Traffic Center . #Norcross residents should avoid westbound JCB at PIB. #GwinnettDOT working on traffic pole. @GwinnettPd @WSBTraffic pic.twitter.com/grUYGmeDwh — Norcross Police (@NorcrossPD) February 23, 2017
